                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The past couple of days that I've played Everquest - have been insanely boring.  Attendance for raids has been slightly lower than normal (one can assume due to new games) and if we're not raiding, we're getting people geared up with epics.  This leaves me a lot of time to think =P
<br />

<br />
I know that a lot of people here have had a problem with bards...myself included, I find it slightly unfair the abilities they have when it comes to initial lockdown with mez/CC duty's in and out of camp.  I've never found the need to rant, seeing as my regular exp group consists of a bard - but I started thinking "What would put me back up to par with a bard on initial locking down of mobs, but wouldn't make me insanely overpowered"
<br />

<br />
I've seen a lot of people who want Fading Memories - I'd *like* Fading Memories, but I don't see this as a viable option for our class for a few reasons that have been beaten to death in previous posts.
<br />

<br />
So - back to the original topic.  Stasis - and my problems with it.
<br />
Where stasis lies now - is it's 72 min recast, 2 second cast time, max level 70 unresistable mez.  It has it's uses, but I feel that we were shafted on this ability as a whole.
<br />

<br />
What I feel should of been done, is make it the enchanters alternative to Fading Memories.  Firstly, make it max level 73.  I think it was idiotic to not have the currently semi useless ability level 73.  Make it cost mana (lets say...1k mana), but have a very very short reuse time.  (say, 5-10 seconds...like an FD reuse) but make the casting time instant.  This would at least supply some alternative to what to do on a resisted mez.  The mana cost is high enough to where you wouldn't use it as a primary mez, but the ability to cast while running (at the cost of a huge amount of mana) would at least give us another option than stand and try and channel another mez.  For all I care, you can make the duration of it only 30 seconds - I've had no use for a 3 minute mez anyway...except in rathe when I gotta go bio =P
<br />

<br />
I danno, just something I've given a huge amount of thought to.
<br />

<br />
I wanna be able to CC shit again - not slow single pulls =P</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
