                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't think it would have killed them to make stasis an instant cast.  The reuse timer certainly is high enough that it really couldn't be flagrantly abused, and bards can already mez while running so there is even some precedent for it.
<br />

<br />
As has already been pointed out, it is not capped at 70.  I use it in Riftseekers frequently and everything there is over level 70. 
<br />

<br />
I do continue to find the whole 'fading memories' theme to be interesting though.  Clerics have a new AA in OOW that isn't 'quite' fading memories but it is really nice.  They can drop themselves to the bottom of the aggro list, and stay there.  It breaks if they cast, and if the group wipes they still get owned, they just get owned last, but it is an aggro control tool for them.  I have no idea why something similar couldn't have been a part of Doppleganger (something like, as long as Dopple is alive, you are at the bottom of the list).  Of course, since Dopple can live for quite a while, that would have to be tuned or it would be abused <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
