                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Enchanters are nukeing slow class with decent buffs and a weak DPS pet.  In a 10 minute fight, we can out DPS <span style="font-weight: bold">wizards</span> -- asking for more is unreasonable.
<br />

<br />
Mezzing is a secondary ability for Enchanters.  Asking for us to be good at mezzing or charming, and for those to be our contributions to a group's success, isn't reasonable -- that would make enchanters <span style="font-style: italic">different</span> than the other cloth classes in qualitative ways.
<br />

<br />
Bards are the primary mezzers/pullers/crowd controllers in EQ.  Such an ability as described would infringe upon their territory.
<br />

<br />
For balance reasons, classes may be buffers, slowers, healers, tanks or melee/pet/spell DPS, or pullers.  All of these abilities may be carefully scaled and controlled.  The same zone with the mobs increased by 5 levels, with 30% more hps and 30% more DPS, is a 30% harder challenge for a group that contains classes with the above catagories.  This makes zone design easier, and that lets SOE spend less time on zone design -- which is a good thing.
<br />

<br />
End sillyness.  The above is not to be taken seriously, especially if you are an EQ dev.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
