                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Soothing Words is one of my favorite AA's with OOW - I've saved countless lives with it.  I've also killed a few people - but definitely saved more than I've killed =p
<br />

<br />
Here is the problem that I see with lowering us to the bottom of the aggro list on a resist.  Lets use the example of a 3 mob pull...warrior is pulling in this example =P  3 mobs come in, warrior goes defensive because he'll explode if more than 1 mob is hitting him at once.  I attempt to mez 1 of the adds - and have a resist.  Meanwhile the cleric lands a heal bomb from the warrior tanking 2.  Cleric gets aggro off 1 mob - I drop myself to bottom of aggro list, cleric has 2 mobs...and gets totally prisonraped.
<br />

<br />
Now, lets say best case scenerio - warrior maintains aggro via AE taunt.  I can still have 2-3 resists on a mez in a row on just about any MPG/RSS mob - so it's not my skill with mezzing, or the clerics timing on heals, or any of that.  It's just subjecting us more to rng on whether or not the group is going to win or wipe.  
<br />

<br />
While I'm on the topic of having so many consecutive mez resists, and relying on RNG for our success as players.
<br />

<br />
WHY THE HELL ARE OOW MOBS SO MR? &gt;_&lt;
<br />

<br />
If it's to make slow more difficult to land, that's fine - I can at least somewhat understand that logic.  More of a -mr mod on Felicity/Euphoria is definitely in order tho.
<br />

<br />
