                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yup, I am kinda bumped that Stasis is not instant cast, cosindering the re-use time, it should be! But oh well, serves its purposes on the rare ocasions that you get a multipull (pretty much never, you lucky to click on mez once every 30 minutes), or a named comes with 1 add (sometimes) and you need to lock the add ASAP cause you are on slow duty as well. Stasis is very situational being 72 mins cast, and sadly it is often back up the next time you have to use it. 
<br />

<br />
Soothing Words is a great AA for saving the cleric, but if your mez gets resisted and your Mind Over Matter AA and/or ER AA happen to be down, I have used it on myself and coupled with a boggle it will make the mob switch its focus to the tank who is holding agro on the other mob.
<br />

<br />
I dont have any problems with mezzing, what I have problems with is the lack of mez content, and no charm to make up for it, making playing a chantie pretty dull nowadays. Not even my Time Lapse procing stick (750 DD) makes up for it, which crits for 1556 (and my melee crits dont cut it either, althought its amussing. I should get my melee crits AA done!).
<br />

<br />
Mind over Matter is an awsome AA, and while up I notice the rune last longer, so it might still "work as intended" for even though I am not taking DMG it sure seems 50% of the DMG is offed because I can take more hits before rune fades. As is, I only got rank2 because about 50% of the times Mind over Matter will fade due to timer without being fully used up.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I know that a lot of people here have had a problem with bards...myself included, I find it slightly unfair the abilities they have when it comes to initial lockdown with mez/CC duty's in and out of camp</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Define "unfair". Each class abilities were spelled out up front when the game came life. If you wanted bard abilities, then you should have made a bard. I understand that the game evolved and that now most of the chanter abilities are phased out, or in other words, SoE didnt not give a crap and chose to ignore (negate would be a better word) the chanter's role in the highend game. But a bard casting on the run today is not unfair all of the sudden because chanters have no defined role in the highend game today. Bard casting on the run is just as unfair today as it was at day 1 of EQ. Seems to me the number 1 issue for those chanters that have "issues" with bards is... they are playing the wrong class, or at some point, they should have made a bard.
<br />

<br />
I made my bard just over a year ago, not because the bard abilities were "unfair" or anything, but rather because I grew bored with chanter having all the AAs done, killing the same mobs over and over for even more AAs was just getting old, either in groups or Charm soloing. But one day at MS camp in BoT, no one wanted the forsaken drum, so we all rolled and agreed to "force" the lowest roller to loot it. Needless to say I looted it, and it remained at bank collecting dust for months.
<br />

<br />
In fact, I didnt know anything about bards when I made mine, was pure chance. Well, once way back then, I was leveling some alt at South Karana and there was a bard kiting gnolls, so I watched for a minute and asked "how long can you do that?", the answer was "As long as I want", to which I replied "You dont go OOM?" and the bard lady said "I dont use mana". After that I walked about my business thinking "Dang! One day I am gonna have to make a bard" (guess I could have thought "Dang! How unfair", and then /petition Nerf bards!, but didnt. Instead I made a bard years later).
<br />

<br />
Just over 1 year old, my bard is level 70 and has over 300 AAs. Sure, my bard has no raid items and its not uber, and her weapons are kinda sucky (has epic though). Still I am ok geared, enuff to perform my bard duties anywhere (Odium camp in MPG gets owned with bard, pulling Disco and Snake named). Except Elementals or PoTime, I aint going thru that hell again.
<br />

<br />
And prolly in 200AAs, when I get done with my bard usefull AAs and not having such a blast anymore, due to pulling tiredom or what not, if I am still playing EQ, I will prolly pick up my 65 necro with 80AAs and level her to 70. But, alas, I fear I will be LFGing forever (70AAs of the 80AAs my necro has were done soloing mobs at HoH, with LFG up).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
