I haven't spent any time at all in RSS yet, so I have nothing to comment there.....
<br />

<br />
I'm still with a group camping a named mob up in the far far far NE corner of MPG.  It's got some hammer that my guild MT wants.  It's a bit of a challenge to get to, due to between 2 and 5 see invis mobs that can spawn on the path there.  And there are even a couple spots where mobs are close enough and/or right around the corner that when you pull one, the other always joins in.  While it's not a lot, I do actually get to heave around my level 67 mezz spell (Felicity?).  Resisted mezz's are pretty much limited to the Lightning mobs.  Lately, it seems to be about 1 in 4 casts on the lightning mobs does NOT get resisted.  Other mobs (Kyv, ukun, noc, etc) I don't have nearly the issue.  Heck, I don't usually get resisted more than 1 in 20 on the non-Lightnings.
<br />

<br />
Although I am a bit worried about the state of enchanters...  just from an incident I had the other day.
<br />

<br />
Time geared pally was pulling/tanking for us at Odium.  Had a shaman in the group, so I was 3rd rate dps with nukes and to make myself feel useful I was tossing Synapsis Spasm.  I've heard it's not worth the mana, but what the heck.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, the pally pulls in an ukun with a noc follower.  So of course I heave out a mezz on the noc.  It lands fine, I drop me hotkey saying it's mezzed and start to debuff the other one.  Next thing I know, I'm sitting at my bind point scrolling up to see what happened.  Seems the pally broke my mezz.  So, I was a bit irate on that, trying to figure out wtf he was doing.  No response.  I'm getting extremely annoyed now, but not as much as usual.  Group wiped from it, so I get a small sense of joy knowing he killed everyone and not just me.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, they find a cleric in the zone running through to a trial to click rez ours.  Everyone gets rez'd.  And of course 3 of the members have to head off because their respective guilds call raids.  Think two went off to Time, the other to GoD somewhere... anyway... 
<br />

<br />
About 5 minutes later I get this window scrolling /tell from the pally.  Apologizing for breaking my mezz.  Said he's gotten so used to enchanters not even bothering to mezz the adds because the just die, that he doesn't even pay attention to the group chat so he missed my mezz message.
<br />

<br />
I still don't know how to take that... is it a compliment to me that I was able to mezz?  Or just a sad stating of fact that enchanters out there are afraid to do their lot in life?
<br />

<br />
I die a lot.  Heck, I'm the Guild Corpse, aka Raid Speedbump.  Even if I was getting resisted more in MPG, I'd like to think I'd still try to do my CC job.  Even if it's harder, and SoE gets a sick kick out of keeping tabs on how many resists cause enchanter deaths.
<br />

<br />
I haven't been so... excited about landing a mezz and not dying from the effort in a long time.  Sure, it's a sad lot we've been handed.  But I'm trying to keep my hard learned CC skills at least somewhat fresh...</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1066832" target="_blank" class="postlink">Maatogaeoth Agryth`Dyrr</a>
